  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In the whole landscape of atomic nuclei, 229 Th is currently the only known nucleus which could allow for the development of a nuclear-based frequency standard, as it possesses an isomeric state of just 7.6 eV energy above the ground state. The 3+ charge state is of special importance in this context, as Th 3+ allows for a simple laser-cooling scheme. Here we emphasize the direct extraction of triply-charged 229 Th from a buffer-gas stopping cell. This finding will not only simplify any future approach of 229 Th ion cooling, but is also used for thorium-beam purification and in this way provides a powerful tool for the direct identification of the 229 Th isomer to ground state nuclear transition.</subfield>
